The paper proposes a model for decision making that can be used by computer programs, which suggests it falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The model also focuses on how people make decisions, which suggests it could also be categorized under Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The use of probabilities and preferences in the model suggests it could also be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the model's emphasis on transparency and explanation suggests it could also be categorized under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
